  "local_port": 36432,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best Olimar strategy in Project M?",
  "response": "Olimar in *Project M* (P:M) is a unique and versatile character with a strong emphasis on Pikmin management and strategic play. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the best strategies to maximize his potential:\n\n---\n\n### **Core Gameplay Tips**\n1. **Pikmin Management**:\n   - Always keep track of your Pikmin lineup. Each Pikmin type has different strengths and weaknesses (Red = fire, Yellow = electric, Blue = water, Purple = heavy, White = poison).\n   - Optimal Pikmin order is situational, but generally, having Purple Pikmin for knockback and White Pikmin for damage-over-time is ideal.\n   - Pluck Pikmin frequently to maintain a full line (up to 6) and replace weaker Pikmin.\n\n2. **Pikmin Toss (Neutral Special)**:\n   - Use Pikmin Toss to pressure opponents from a distance. Attached Pikmin deal damage over time and can disrupt your opponent\u2019s movement.\n   - Mix up the timing and direction of your tosses to keep your opponent guessing.\n\n3. **Whistle (Down Special)**:\n   - Use the whistle to reorganize your Pikmin lineup. This is especially useful for bringing Purple or White Pikmin to the front.\n   - The whistle also grants brief invincibility, which can be used to escape combos or avoid attacks.\n\n---\n\n### **Neutral Game**\n- **Space with Pikmin Toss**: Place Pikmin on your opponent to force them to react. This can limit their movement and create openings.\n- **Dashes and Tilts**:\n  - Use your dash attack for quick damage and approach.\n  - Forward tilt and up tilt are quick and effective for poking and setting up combos.\n- **Grab Game**:\n  - Olimar\u2019s grab is one of his strongest tools. Use it often to start combos or rack up damage.\n  - Down throw is great for combos, while forward and back throws can KO at high percents.\n\n---\n\n### **Combo Game**\n- **Pikmin Chain (Up Special)**:\n  - This move can be used both as a recovery and a surprise attack. It\u2019s great for hitting opponents offstage or extending combos.\n- **Aerials**:\n  - Neutral air is a solid combo starter and can juggle opponents.\n  - Forward air is strong for spacing and can KO at high percents.\n  - Down air is a powerful spike and can be used for edge-guarding.\n- **Combos**:\n  - Down throw \u2192 up air \u2192 neutral air is a simple and effective combo.\n  - Forward throw \u2192 forward air can work at lower percents.\n  - Use Purple Pikmin for knockback-heavy attacks to secure KOs.\n\n---\n\n### **Edge-Guarding**\n- **Pikmin Toss**: Toss Pikmin at recovering opponents to limit their options.\n- **Spikes**: Use down air or Pikmin Chain to spike opponents offstage.\n- **Purple Pikmin**: Save Purple Pikmin for edge-guarding, as their high knockback can easily secure stocks.\n\n---\n\n### **Recovery**\n- **Pikmin Chain**: Be mindful of your recovery angle and timing, as it\u2019s somewhat predictable.\n- **Whistle**: Use the whistle\u2019s invincibility frames to avoid edge-guards.\n- **Mix Up Recovery**: Use a combination of Pikmin Chain, air dodges, and wall jumps (if applicable) to make your recovery less predictable.\n\n---\n\n### **Advanced Techniques**\n- **Pikmin Cycling**: Use the whistle to cycle through your Pikmin quickly and optimize your lineup.\n- **Pikmin Toss Pressure**: Attach Pikmin to your opponent and pressure them with aerials or grabs while they try to remove the Pikmin.\n- **Shield Breaks**: Purple Pikmin\u2019s side smash can break shields if timed correctly.\n\n---\n\n### **Matchup-Specific Tips**\n- **Against Fast Characters**: Focus on spacing and Pikmin Toss to keep them at bay.\n- **Against Heavyweights**: Use combos and Purple Pikmin to rack up damage and secure KOs.\n- **Against Campy Characters**: Use Pikmin Toss to apply pressure and force them to approach.\n\n---\n\nBy mastering Pikmin management, spacing, and Olimar\u2019s combo potential, you can dominate in *Project M*. Practice and adaptability are key to becoming a strong Olimar player!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
